Yesterday, a group of friends and I attended trivia for Grey's Anatomy night (which was so much fun and the host was great) at this establishment. I arrived around 6:20pm, where 2 of my friends who had been there had already had 2 rounds of drinks and their appetizers. I wound up ordering drinks from the bar because our server (long long hair and huge hoop earrings, I believe her name is Stasi) never came over when we arrived until 7:10 pm. 50 minutes, she never even came to check on our table or greet the new guests. The guy bartender (didn't catch his name but he was AWESOME) let me start a tab and apologized for the service we were receiving. At 7:10 pm, we flagged down the server and she walked over looking super confused. She said she forgot we were her table. For 50 minutes, she "forgot" we were her table, the table she had been serving drinks and food too before I even showed up. We ordered food. Nothing crazy but for some reason it took over an hour for chicken and waffles and a nashville hot chicken sandwich (both which were delicious) I get the kitchen is slammed but that wasn't the case of why we waited an hour for our food. When the server finally brought the food, the tin trays were scalding hot as if they had been in the window for 30 minutes. The manager on duty was too busy helping bartenders due to not enough staff on a busy night (trivia and a concert next door) to acknowledge the issues going on in this establishment. Very Sad.
